text: Antigo ( )Webster's New Geographical Dictionary (G. & C. Merriam Co., 1972), p. 57. is a city in and the county seat of Langlade County, Wisconsin, United States. The population was 8,100 at the 2020 census. The name "Antigo" comes from the Chippewa Indian name for the river that flows through the area, "Nequi-Antigo-sebi" meaning "spring river" or "evergreen." ==References== Category:Cities in Wisconsin Category:County seats in Wisconsin Category:Langlade County, Wisconsin
title: Antigo, Wisconsin
